Lingua-BioYaTeA version 0.1
================================

(version of YaTeA - Yet Another Term ExtrActor - tuned for Biomedical
texts)

BioYaTeA is a module implementing a version of the configurable term
extractor YaTeA for biomedical texts. It recognizes term candidates in
corpora. It can also take into account testified terms issued from
terminological resources.

Contains this script :

    bioyatea

(see MANIFEST for all the files)

INSTALLATION

It requires Mdoule::Build version 0.28 (at least) and File::chmod


To install this module type the following:

   perl Build.PL
   Build
   Build test
   Build install

Or if you like better the "make" program:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

 Module::Build
 File::chmod
 Lingua::YaTeA >= 0.6

 If one of those modules are not installed, download it from
 http://search.cpan.org and run the installation script (see the
 README), or use the cpan command (switch as root or administrator
 account if necessary):

   cpan module

   For instance: cpan Config::General

   It will check the dependencies and install the module. 

DOCUMENTATION

See the documentation in the module (man bioyatea and man Lingua::BioYaTeA)

